comments.text:
+iggykoopa123 If you dive into the water in such a way that you're not 
piercing in (piercing in meaning like the professionals or anyone who jumps 
from a high altitude does) and instead you're just opposing resistance to 
the water, the impact could be as strong if not stronger than if you fell 
on concrete from that height. Don't believe me? Next time you're in a pool, 
make a high five and slap the water surface a couple of times. Then make a 
fist and try to punch the water from above. You're gonna notice a huge 
difference.
